history.content: Hello, CS students!  Are you interested in trying an experimental programming tutorial?  I’m a student researcher in UC Berkeley EECS.  We’re conducting a study on improving CS education--specifically to find out if exciting new programming tools can help students learn CS.  Study sessions are 90 minutes, and participants will receive a $30 Amazon giftcard.  If you think you might be interested, please sign up at https://tinyurl.com/introcsstudy!  (Don’t worry, filling out the Google form isn’t a commitment to participate!)  And if you have any questions, feel free to email me at dhanyajayagopal@berkeley.edu.
history.subject: Compensated CS Research Study!
